review_blob: Too skunky, does not have the flavor of the regular lager, wouldnt drink it again
Skunky, not too great, but is smooth and lot better than the light version.
A bit sweet and flat, however tasty and smooth. Not very bitter and not much of a aftertaste.
Too skunky, kind of smooth, but would rather have most domestic lights for half the price.
One of my favorite beers so far, up there with dogfish 90 and three floyds pale ale. Great dinner drink, has a lot flavor, and fills you up pretty good. Not easy to find in PA though.
Favorite beer so far that can be purchased at almost any distributor. Has a lot of flavor, fair amount of bitterness but is also easy to drink.

First rating, figured i start with the one i just recently had. Compared to other lagers that are marketed to the masses this beer offers the best taste. It is reasonably light and easy to drink. Solid choice if consuming a fair amount.
